Let's diagnose! Common particle issues:

**1. Too few particles = sparse and weak**
```
Before:  · · ·     (sad)
After:   ········· (better!)
```

**2. Wrong lifetime = disappear too fast or linger**
```
Before:  appears ──→ gone instantly
After:   appears ──→ fades gracefully ──→ gone
```

**3. No variation = robotic and fake**
```
Before:  [same][same][same]
After:   [big][small][medium][tiny]
```

Here's a polished particle template:

```holo
composition "Good Particles" {

  // BEFORE: Basic bad particles
  particle BadFire {
    count: 10
    color: "#ff6600"
    lifetime: 0.5
    size: 1
    speed: 5
  }

  // AFTER: Good fire particles
  particle GoodFire {
    // More particles!
    count: 50
    emit_rate: 30  // Per second

    // Color gradient over lifetime
    color: {
      start: "#ffff00",  // Yellow core
      mid: "#ff6600",    // Orange
      end: "#ff0000"     // Red tips
    }
    opacity: {
      start: 1.0,
      end: 0  // Fade out
    }

    // Size variation
    size: {
      start: { min: 0.2, max: 0.5 },
      end: { min: 0.05, max: 0.1 }  // Shrink
    }

    // Lifetime variation
    lifetime: { min: 0.5, max: 1.5 }

    // Movement
    speed: { min: 1, max: 3 }
    direction: { 
      base: [0, 1, 0],  // Up
      spread: 30        // Cone angle
    }
    gravity: -0.5  // Rises (negative = up)

    // Rotation for more organic look
    rotation: { min: 0, max: 360 }
    rotation_speed: { min: -90, max: 90 }  // Degrees/sec

    // Blending
    blend_mode: "additive"  // Glowy!
    texture: "soft_circle"
  }

  // Explosion burst
  particle Explosion {
    count: 100
    emit_mode: "burst"  // All at once

    color: {
      start: "#ffffff",
      mid: "#ffaa00",
      end: "#ff3300"
    }
    opacity: { start: 1, end: 0 }

    size: { start: 0.5, end: 2 }  // Grow!

    lifetime: { min: 0.3, max: 0.8 }

    speed: { min: 5, max: 15 }
    direction: { base: "outward", spread: 180 }  // All directions

    gravity: 2  // Falls down after burst

    blend_mode: "additive"
  }

  // Sparkle/magic dust
  particle MagicDust {
    count: 30
    emit_rate: 20

    color: ["#66ffff", "#ff66ff", "#ffff66"]  // Random from list
    opacity: { start: 0, peak: 1, end: 0 }  // Fade in AND out

    size: { start: 0.1, end: 0.05 }

    lifetime: { min: 1, max: 2 }

    speed: { min: 0.2, max: 0.5 }
    direction: { base: "random" }

    // Twinkle effect
    flicker: { 
      enabled: true,
      frequency: 5,
      intensity: 0.5
    }

    blend_mode: "additive"
    texture: "star_4point"
  }

  // Smoke
  particle Smoke {
    count: 20
    emit_rate: 10

    color: { start: "#666666", end: "#333333" }
    opacity: { start: 0.6, end: 0 }

    size: { start: 0.3, end: 2 }  // Expands

    lifetime: { min: 2, max: 4 }

    speed: { min: 0.5, max: 1 }
    direction: { base: [0, 1, 0], spread: 20 }
    gravity: -0.2

    // Drift sideways
    noise: {
      enabled: true,
      scale: 0.3,
      speed: 0.5
    }

    blend_mode: "normal"  // Not additive for smoke
    texture: "cloud_soft"
  }
}
```

**Quick reference - what makes particles look good:**

| Property | Bad | Good |
|----------|-----|------|
| Count | 10 | 50-100 |
| Size | Fixed | Varies + changes over time |
| Opacity | Fixed | Fades out |
| Color | Single | Gradient over lifetime |
| Speed | Fixed | Range (min/max) |
| Lifetime | Fixed | Range |
| Texture | Square | Soft circle/custom |
| Blend | Normal | Additive for glows |

**The flow of a good particle:**
```
[Spawn] ──→ [Fade in] ──→ [Full opacity] ──→ [Fade out] ──→ [Die]
   │           │              │                 │
 small      growing        at peak           shrinking
 transparent  visible       bright            fading
```

Try swapping your bad particles for these templates and see the difference!

Fishing games are **timing-based flow loops**:

```
[Cast Line] ──→ [Wait] ──→ [Bite!] ──→ [Reel Minigame] ──→ [Catch/Fail]
     │                        │              │
   click                   timing!        skill test
```

**The classic fishing loop:**

```holo
composition "Fishing Minigame" {

  // Fishing states
  const FishingState = {
    IDLE: "idle",
    CASTING: "casting",
    WAITING: "waiting",
    BITE: "bite",
    REELING: "reeling",
    CAUGHT: "caught",
    ESCAPED: "escaped"
  }

  // Current fishing session
  const Fishing = {
    state: FishingState.IDLE,
    current_fish: null,
    tension: 50,      // 0-100, fish escapes at extremes
    progress: 0,      // 0-100, catch at 100
    bite_window: 0    // Time left to react
  }

  // Fish data
  const FishTypes = {
    "common_carp": { name: "Carp", difficulty: 0.3, value: 10, weight: [1, 5] },
    "bass": { name: "Bass", difficulty: 0.5, value: 25, weight: [2, 8] },
    "golden_trout": { name: "Golden Trout", difficulty: 0.8, value: 100, weight: [1, 3] },
    "legendary_catfish": { name: "Old Whiskers", difficulty: 1.0, value: 500, weight: [15, 30] }
  }

  // UI Elements
  ui FishingUI {
    // Tension meter (keep in green zone)
    meter TensionBar {
      position: { bottom: 100, center: true }
      width: 300
      zones: {
        danger_low: { range: [0, 20], color: "red" },
        safe: { range: [20, 80], color: "green" },
        danger_high: { range: [80, 100], color: "red" }
      }
    }

    // Progress bar
    meter ProgressBar {
      position: { bottom: 150, center: true }
      width: 300
      color: "#00ffff"
    }

    // Bite indicator
    icon BiteAlert {
      position: { center: true }
      sprite: "exclamation"
      visible: false
      scale: 2
    }
  }

  logic {
    // Start fishing on interact with water
    on_interact("water") where Player.has_item("fishing_rod") {
      start_casting()
    }

    // CAST PHASE
    function start_casting() {
      Fishing.state = FishingState.CASTING
      Player.play_animation("cast_line")
      audio.play("cast_whoosh")

      after(1000) {
        start_waiting()
      }
    }

    // WAITING PHASE
    function start_waiting() {
      Fishing.state = FishingState.WAITING
      ui.toast("Waiting for a bite...")

      // Random wait time
      let wait_time = random(3000, 15000)

      after(wait_time) {
        // Pick a fish based on location, time, bait, etc.
        Fishing.current_fish = pick_fish()
        start_bite()
      }
    }

    function pick_fish() {
      // Weighted random selection
      let roll = random()
      if (roll < 0.05) return FishTypes.legendary_catfish
      if (roll < 0.2) return FishTypes.golden_trout
      if (roll < 0.5) return FishTypes.bass
      return FishTypes.common_carp
    }

    // BITE PHASE - Player must react!
    function start_bite() {
      Fishing.state = FishingState.BITE
      Fishing.bite_window = 1500  // 1.5 seconds to react

      // Alert!
      FishingUI.BiteAlert.visible = true
      FishingUI.BiteAlert.pulse()
      audio.play("splash_bite")
      camera.shake(0.2, 0.3)

      // Countdown
      let timer = setInterval(() => {
        Fishing.bite_window -= 100
        if (Fishing.bite_window <= 0) {
          clearInterval(timer)
          fish_escaped("Too slow!")
        }
      }, 100)
    }

    // Player clicks during bite = start reeling
    on_click() where Fishing.state == FishingState.BITE {
      FishingUI.BiteAlert.visible = false
      start_reeling()
    }

    // REELING PHASE - The actual minigame
    function start_reeling() {
      Fishing.state = FishingState.REELING
      Fishing.tension = 50
      Fishing.progress = 0

      FishingUI.TensionBar.visible = true
      FishingUI.ProgressBar.visible = true

      ui.toast("Keep tension in the green zone!")
    }

    // Reeling game loop
    every(50) where Fishing.state == FishingState.REELING {
      let fish = Fishing.current_fish

      // Fish pulls (increases tension)
      let pull = fish.difficulty * random(0.5, 2)
      Fishing.tension += pull

      // Player holding click = reel in (decreases tension, gains progress)
      if (Input.mouse_down) {
        Fishing.tension -= 3
        Fishing.progress += 1 - fish.difficulty * 0.5
        Player.play_animation("reeling")
      } else {
        // Not reeling = tension builds, progress slips
        Fishing.tension += 1
        Fishing.progress -= 0.2
      }

      // Fish occasionally jerks (spikes tension)
      if (random() < 0.02) {
        Fishing.tension += 20
        audio.play("splash")
        camera.shake(0.3, 0.2)
      }

      // Clamp values
      Fishing.tension = clamp(Fishing.tension, 0, 100)
      Fishing.progress = clamp(Fishing.progress, 0, 100)

      // Update UI
      FishingUI.TensionBar.value = Fishing.tension
      FishingUI.ProgressBar.value = Fishing.progress

      // Check win/lose
      if (Fishing.tension <= 5) {
        fish_escaped("Line went slack!")
      } else if (Fishing.tension >= 95) {
        fish_escaped("Line snapped!")
      } else if (Fishing.progress >= 100) {
        fish_caught()
      }
    }

    function fish_caught() {
      Fishing.state = FishingState.CAUGHT
      let fish = Fishing.current_fish
      let weight = random(fish.weight[0], fish.weight[1])

      FishingUI.TensionBar.visible = false
      FishingUI.ProgressBar.visible = false

      Player.play_animation("catch_fish")
      audio.play("success_jingle")
      spawn_particles("water_splash", Player.position)

      // Add to inventory
      Player.add_item({
        id: fish.id,
        name: fish.name,
        weight: weight,
        value: fish.value
      })

      // Show result
      ui.show_catch_screen({
        fish: fish.name,
        weight: weight.toFixed(1) + " lbs",
        value: fish.value + " gold"
      })

      after(3000) {
        Fishing.state = FishingState.IDLE
      }
    }

    function fish_escaped(reason) {
      Fishing.state = FishingState.ESCAPED

      FishingUI.TensionBar.visible = false
      FishingUI.ProgressBar.visible = false
      FishingUI.BiteAlert.visible = false

      audio.play("fail_sound")
      ui.toast("The fish got away! " + reason)

      after(2000) {
        Fishing.state = FishingState.IDLE
      }
    }

    // Cancel fishing
    on_key("Escape") where Fishing.state != FishingState.IDLE {
      Fishing.state = FishingState.IDLE
      FishingUI.TensionBar.visible = false
      FishingUI.ProgressBar.visible = false
      FishingUI.BiteAlert.visible = false
    }
  }
}
```

**The state machine:**
```
[IDLE] ──click water──→ [CASTING] ──1s──→ [WAITING]
                                              │
                                        random time
                                              │
                                              ↓
[IDLE] ←──────────── [ESCAPED] ←──fail── [BITE] ──click──→ [REELING]
   ↑                                                          │
   │                                                    keep tension
   │                                                     in green
   │                                                          │
   └─────────────── [CAUGHT] ←──progress 100%─────────────────┘
```

